                        "__typename": "EmployerReviewRG",
                        "advice": "EF should strongly reconsider their practices in regards to overtime for teachers. They expect lessons to be planned in 9 hours for a week when you have what they qualify as 30 ACH. More classes means I should be given more money and more prep time not the same amount. Why is it not calculated into my schedule that I need so many minutes to plan small stars as opposed to high flyers or TB? \r\n\r\nTeachers that actually care about their students stay and plan after work hours but are we compensated no. I went from 24 ACH to 29ACH where does the extra time to plan the additional classes come from? No where. It's flabbergasting how this company is worth so much but cannot even compensate their current teachers for classes. No wonder why people leave so quickly at EF. \r\n\r\nIn reality anything over  25 ACH should be considered overtime.",
